CURRENT LICENSE
---------------

Peko Agent is licensed under the **GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 or
later (AGPL-3.0-or-later)**. The full text is in `LICENSE-AGPL`.

Under AGPL, any software that uses, modifies, or distributes Peko Agent —
including over a network (see AGPL §13) — must also be released under the
AGPL and make its Corresponding Source Code available to users.

COMMERCIAL LICENSE (PLANNED, NOT YET AVAILABLE)
-----------------------------------------------

A commercial license allowing proprietary use without AGPL's source-disclosure
requirements is planned but has not been finalized or reviewed by counsel.
Until then, **no commercial license is available**, and the only way to use
Peko Agent is under AGPL-3.0-or-later. See `LICENSE-COMMERCIAL` for status and
contact information.

THIRD-PARTY SOFTWARE
--------------------

This project incorporates third-party software licensed under other terms
(notably MIT-licensed code from cpp-httplib, nlohmann/json, llama.cpp, and
ggml). These licenses are preserved in source form and their full texts are
reproduced in `third_party/LICENSES/`. See `NOTICE.md` for the consolidated
attribution list.

AGPL allows incorporation of MIT-licensed code; the combined work is governed
by the AGPL, but the original MIT notices must remain with the third-party
portions.

AGPL §13 — NETWORK USE
----------------------

If you deploy Peko Agent as a network-accessible service (web UI, bot,
scheduled agent, etc.), you must offer the Corresponding Source to every
user interacting with it remotely, including users of any modifications
you make. The built-in web UI exposes a link to the upstream source for
this purpose.
